It&#8217;s a &#8220;matter of time&#8221; before the detective boss, who has put so many killers behind bars, lose his fight with his own serial killer.Piet Byleveld was admitted to the Wilgeheuwel Hospital in Roodepoort on Tuesday. &#8220;The doctors told me this morning that it could be any time,&#8221; said Elize, his wife.Piet was diagnosed with phase four lung cancer which spread to his adrenal gland and liver. &#8220;We try to keep him as comfortable as possible. &#8220;I spend my days sleeping next to his bed,&#8221; Elize said emotionally over the phone. Piet captured many killers like the Wemer Pan killer and Leigh Matthews&#8217;s killer Donovan Moodley.